node.text:
No, it’s not an onlyfans lol its better! Although that’s what is expected of me, I like to break the mold. Go against the grain and counter culture. Showing myself and others that you can be anything you decided to be. Don’t apologize for being true to yourself, whatever that may be. 

From starting off in men’s magazines like maxim in lingerie and swimsuits.. to crossing over into the fitness world and landing big contacts that changed my life… I was able to invest into my interests and make them businesses becoming an entrepreneur at a young age and learning some of the hardest lessons. I’m sure some of you remember superfitbabes & bodybyorsini both were great teachers and my 1st loves in business. Also my 1st heartbreaks.

Pain is a great teacher & motivator if your willing to learn. It prepared me for @orsiniworld my Diamond jewlery line that is a dream come true. 

… Now this is the beginning of a new chapter and another great dream fulfilled. Making money is amazing but I want to use my influence for a higher purpose. Big money & helping lots of people is the goal. To help others achieve financial freedom and to have control over their own lives because I truly believe we are all ment for more. 

That’s why I launched @higherinfluencesociety today, to build a strong culture of community that believes in enriching their lives through education, self development, and consistency. (I’ll be mentoring you.) This is your invitation. The link is in my bio, sign up for our 1st call that is tomorrow night. See you then! 

I can’t wait to see what you will become!

Follow @higherinfluencesociety to stay up to date on our calls. ✨

#higherinfluencesociety

node.text:
The quality of your life is dependent on the quality of your relationships. 
.
.
These beautiful children warmed my heart this morning. I was moved with tears. What a beautiful reminder of what’s is truly important. 
.
.
Family is forever but we won’t always be here. Do more, show up more, love more, today. Because today is all we have. Tomorrow is promised to no one. 
.
.
In a world that is so loud. Fighting for your attention to buy this, watch that, consume this, etc. Take your power back. Choose. Decide what’s important to you and act on it daily. 
.
.
❤️

node.text:
We pulled up to the famous SS Sapona Shipwreck ❤️ so much wildlife, amazing diving site in Bimini. 

So the SS Sapona was a concrete-hulled cargo steamer that ran aground near Bimini during a hurricane in 1926. The wreck of the ship is still super visible above the water, it’s huge, and now it’s both a navigational landmark for boaters & divers. 

To many more adventures with you @isellmoney

node.text:
Happy Independence Day to my fellow Colombians all over the world ❤️❤️❤️ some of my favorite memories there🇨🇴 Proud of my roots in the mother land and I wouldn’t be the woman I am without the influence of strong Colombia women and men in my life. 

I have family there now young & old that I love very much. I know Colombia has been going through a tough time and it feels too familiar. An echo of similarities throughout the world of our freedoms under attack. From the US to Africa, from Nicaragua to Cuba. The world needs unity, prayer, and healing. 

To my Colombians in Colombia. Next election be active and don’t let a communist come into power. Pay close attention and learn from other countries.

node.text:
What you see < what my heart feels. 

So many things on my heart ❤️ I can’t look at this city and not think about the Cuban people. Especially on the water knowing miles away they need help. 

I haven’t posted in a few days because I just couldn’t. 

I know I’m not Cuban but I am from miami and Cubans are a huge part of our culture here and a part of who I am today. Growing up in miami.. they were my best friends, I ate with them, danced with them, slept at their homes. If you know Cubans you know how they share what they do have. How much they love each other and life. They can make anything a good time.

With that being said, I always grew up listening to the stores from their parents and grandparents telling us about Cuba. How they had to shred bed sheets and season it and pretend it was “ropa vieja” (shredded meat) or how people would melt yellow condoms onto a piece of bread and pretend it was pizza. How their father went to jail for a bag of rice.

This is a big moment for them, this is the closest they have gotten to the hope of freedom for all of them. 

Even if you don’t understand be kind to them and listen. Be patient and Learn. Understand what they are fighting for. Why they risk their lives to come here. Why they’re sick and tired. There is a Huge lesson here for us as Americans. Have the balls to watch the videos and see for yourself. These people have suffered decades.

I don’t need to be black to care about black lives, I don’t need to be Israeli or Palestinian to care about their lives. And I don’t need to be Cuban to care about what’s happening to them right now. Human life is human life. All that extra stuff is just division and politics. What if it was you on that island with your family? How would you want the world to respond? 

While I’m over here basking in freedom they are hoping and wishing for it. I pray that this generation wakes up because if this country becomes socialist/communist we will have nowhere else to go. 

❤️
